{"info": {"author": "Maciej Nowak", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Utilities"], "description": "DeferredResult\n---\n\nThis library provides simple deferred result.\n\n# Usage\n\nCreate deferred result:\n```python\ndef_result = DeferredResult[str]()\n``` \n\nThen you can wait for the result using optional timeout:\n```python\nresult = def_result.wait(timeout=1)\n```\n\nWhile waiting for result other thread can set result:\n```python\ndef_result.resolve('Hello World')\n```\n\nAfter resolving result all threads waiting for result will be resumed.\n\nIt is also possible to reject deferred result:\n```python\ndef_result.reject(RuntimeError('Well....'))\n```\n\nIn that case all threads waiting for result will be resumed and exception passed to `reject` will be thrown.", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/Novakov/py-deferred-result", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "deferred-result", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/deferred-result/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/deferred-result/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/Novakov/py-deferred-result"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/deferred-result/0.1.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.7", "summary": "Simple DeferredResult", "version": "0.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h2>DeferredResult</h2>\n<p>This library provides simple deferred result.</p>\n<h1>Usage</h1>\n<p>Create deferred result:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">def_result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">DeferredResult</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nb\">str</span><span class=\"p\">]()</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Then you can wait for the result using optional timeout:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">def_result</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wait</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">timeout</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>While waiting for result other thread can set result:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">def_result</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">resolve</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'Hello World'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>After resolving result all threads waiting for result will be resumed.</p>\n<p>It is also possible to reject deferred result:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">def_result</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">reject</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"ne\">RuntimeError</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'Well....'</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</pre>\n<p>In that case all threads waiting for result will be resumed and exception passed to <code>reject</code> will be thrown.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6485276, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e20e8627342b362f776b49dca514135e", "sha256": "317ccc9e433b983561d5c3ec8c8589b93881e4455c7962a986731ecbecd7b52e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "deferred_result-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e20e8627342b362f776b49dca514135e", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 2159, "upload_time": "2020-01-20T08:20:19", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-20T08:20:19.379099Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7c/e3/6f3ef10c414f693211c2610803d114e8c58e8b95df7f1870b999c3bd7069/deferred_result-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]}, "urls": [{"comment_text": "", 